  "text": "According to UWSNs' characteristics, many researchers have been studying UWSNs routing protocol and have obtained achievements [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . In [CITATION_8] , a novel Path Unaware Layered Routing Protocol (PULRP) was proposed for dense 3D UWSNs. PULRP is proved to have higher PDR compared to the Under-Water Diffusion (UWD) algorithm proposed in [CITATION_9] and Dijkstra's shortest path algorithm. However, a significant limitation in most underwater sensor nodes is low battery capacity. In addition, the transmission range of each node must be optimized to avoid early node failures due to energy depletion. In [CITATION_10] , an Energy Optimized Path Unaware Layered Routing Protocol (E-PULRP) was proposed. E-PULRP algorithm utilizes energy optimized layered structure to reduce the energy loss. It also restricts transmission distance for further energy optimization in the same way. However, E-PULRP algorithm was suitable for a stationary sink node located at the center of the deployment volume. It cannot be applied to UWSNs with multiple mobile sink nodes.",
